over 2000 entries blacklisted : the film lover 's guide to the hollywood blacklist is the collaboratively effort of paul buhle and dave wagner and an alphabetically arranged encyclopedia of entries concerning the films , directors , stars , writers , producers , designers , and others who suffered being blacklisted because of the house un-american activities committee during their infamous hollywood blacklist era . over 2000 entries point the reader in the direction of grand works that were covered in shadow during a dangerous time in american history , including films such as & quot ; roman holiday & quot ; and & quot ; bridge on the river kwai & quot ; . blacklisted is a welcome and greatly appreciated contribution to cinematic studies reference collections